  <h1>OpenFLUID installation instructions for OSX</h1>
  <center>version @README_VERSION_FULL@</center>
  <br/>
  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  OpenFLUID for OSX relies on packages provided by the <a href="http://brew.sh" target="_blank">Homebrew package manager</a>.
  Installation instructions for Homebrew are available on <a href="http://brew.sh" target="_blank">http://brew.sh</a>.<br/>
  <br/>
  Once the Homebrew manager installed, you have to install the following packages:
  <ul>
    <li>cmake</li>
    <li>doxygen</li>
    <li>boost</li>
    <li>qt4</li>
    <li>gdal</li>
    <li>geos</li>
  </ul>
  <i>command line:</i><br/>
  <p><code>brew install cmake doxygen boost qt4 gdal geos</code></p><br/>
  <br/>
  For full usage of OpenFLUID features, the packages below have to be installed (recommended):
  <ul>
    <li>graphviz</li>
    <li>gnuplot</li>
    <li>p7zip</li>
  </ul>
  <i>command line:</i><br/>
  <p><code>brew install graphviz gnuplot p7zip</code></p><br/>
  <br/>

  <h2>Installation of OpenFLUID</h2>
  To install OpenFLUID, double-click on the <tt>@INSTALLER_PKG_NAME@</tt> file and follow the instructions.<br/>
  OpenFLUID will be installed in <tt>@OSXPACK_INSTALL_PREFIX@</tt>
  and shortcuts will be created in the <tt>/Applications</tt> folder.<br/>
  <br/>
  <u>Note:</u> The installation may fail if Homebrew and required packages have not been previously installed.
  <br/>

  <h2>Uninstall</h2>
  There is no automatic tool to uninstall OpenFLUID for OSX.
  You have to manually remove the OpenFLUID shortcuts located in the <tt>/Applications</tt> folder
  and manually remove the files listed below (located in <tt>@OSXPACK_INSTALL_PREFIX@</tt>).
  <br/>
  <pre>@FILES_TO_UNINSTALL@</pre>

</body>
